body:
@narfbg I found it. I'm the one making the second call to the initialize so that I set the rest of the configuration on the controller. You may try it:

config/pagination.php

```
            $config['next_link'] = '<i class="right arrow icon"></i>';
            $config['next_tag_open'] = '<span class="icon item">';
            $config['next_tag_close'] = '</span>';
```

controllers/test.php

```
            $config['base_url'] = base_url("/pesquisa/{$q}");
            $config['total_rows'] = $data['total'];
            $config['per_page'] = 10;
            $this->pagination->initialize($config);
            $data['paginas'] = $this->pagination->create_links();
```

I tried to not use the initialize on the controller, but it doesn't add the rest of the configuration specific to the controller. Maybe the attribution $this->_attributes = '' would be better placed in the constructor or initialize method.

> Your guess is wrong. It was version 3.0.0 (files dated March 30, 2015, 9:57 AM) that I downloaded and installed myself on April 5, 2015.

Ok.

