> > In other words, you're looking in the wrong place.
> 
> Well, that may be true, since I'm only looking for an explanation here.

Sorry, this is a bug tracker - we don't provide such support here, that's what the [forums](http://forum.codeigniter.com/) are for, and we're way off topic at this point.

> So can you simply explain how this pagination.php config file can be used for pagination in all controller functions

I can, but I won't. Sorry.
See above.

> when each controller/function will have at least one pagination setting (such as base_url) that's unique to only that one controller/function?

That's a precondition that _you are asserting_, not one that must always be used and/or true.

> (your code examples here)

You claim that this doesn't work, or can't work, or used to work but now doesn't ... Yet, I've already explained that this can't possibly be caused by `CI_Pagination`.
